    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Database systems that allow institutions to control aspects of collections, including description (artist, title, measurements, media, style, subject, etc.) as well as administrative information regarding acquisitions, loans, and conservation information.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051198/Harpring, Introduction to Controlled Vocabularies (2010)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Databasesystemen waarmee instellingen aspecten van hun collecties beheren en waarin zowel beschrijvingen (kunstenaar, titel, afmetingen, medium, stijl, onderwerp, etc.) als administratieve informatie betreffende aankoop, leningen en conservatie zijn opgenomen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
